sections.title: DAILY VIDEO
sections.description:
If your schedule permits, you may do the training over two sessions. (Example: Any Skill Work + Bonus = Session 1; Strength + Cardio + Accessory = Session 2)

For any training questions, be sure to post in the Flagship/60 2.0 channel in Circle!

sections.title: warmup
sections.description:
3x
15/12 Cal Row
10/10 Rotating Posterior Dumbbell Press
10/10 Trap Stretch On The Rig
20 Banded Face Pull

sections.title: Strength
sections.description:
Dumbbell Bench

3 Sets:
:40 Max Rep Dumbbell Bench // RPE 7
Rest 1:30 Between Sets.

NOTES:
- If you did this last week, use the same weight.
- Perform these with a @ 2020 tempo (i.e. :02 down, no pause at the bottom, :02 up, no pause at the top). Don't game the :40, perform controlled reps for the entire working time.
- Use a load that feels like an RPE 7.
------------
OPTION A.

Strict Pull-Up

5 Sets of Max Reps (Cap @ 12 Reps)
Rest 2:00 Between Sets.

NOTES:
- We are adding one set this week. If you did this last week, aim to complete more total reps than last week.
- This option is for those that either have strict pull-ups but are not ready to load them, or people who do not have strict pull-ups and will need to use a band.
- Use a band if you will get less than five reps on any given set.
- Leave one rep in the tank on each set.
- If you are using bands, use as few bands as possible, and aim for at least 8 reps.
----
OPTION B.

Weighted Strict Pull-Up

6 Sets:
4 Reps @ RPE 8
Rest 1:30 Between Sets.

NOTES:
- Adding one rep this week! Use the same weight as last week.
- Use a load that is challenging but allows you to perform four explosive reps.

sections.title: metcon
sections.description:
AMRAP 14
100ft D-Ball / Sandbag Bear Hug Carry @ 150/100lbs
10 Alternating Front Rack Barbell Lunge @ 155/105lbs
5 Shoulder to Overhead 155/105

NOTES:
- This AMRAP is meant to be a gritty fourteen minutes. Settle in to just chipping away on each movement until the time expires.
- The shoulder-to-overhead should be unbroken. If you need to scale, use 49kg. Or if you are feeling like going RX+, use 185/135lbs.

sections.title: Accessory
sections.description:
Single Arm Dumbbell Strict Press
4x8/8 @ RPE 8
Rest :30 Between Arms.
Rest 1:30 Between Sets.

NOTES:
- Aim to go heavier than last week. You should have 2-3 reps left in the tank on the first set.
----
Rolling Dumbbell Skull Crusher
3x20
Rest 1-2 Minutes Between Sets.

sections.title: bonus
sections.description:
Fan Bike Intervals.
----------
8 Sets of (1:00 On / 1:00 Rest)...
8/6 Cal "Sprint" + 70-80% of Mile Pace *

* i.e. after the sprint, hold 70-80% of your mile pace for the remainder of the minute.

NOTES:
- Your "sprint" should be RPE 9. Leave some in the tank.
- Get to your 70-80% mile pace as soon as possible.
